        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I’d like to thank my editors, who put up with my diva-like refusal to check the accuracy of statistics and facts and just corrected my numerous errors for me. I’d like to thank my friends for graciously allowing me to appropriate their opinions when I couldn’t come up with one of my own. I’d like to thank my family and fiancée for reading my columns when they remembered to.</p>
<p>And, of course, I’d like to thank you, my readers, not only for sticking with me to the end of this remarkably (even for me) self-indulgent column, but for sticking with me for six years. I could not have done it without you, and even if I could have, I wouldn’t have wanted to. </p>
<p><em>Alex Fanaroff is a fourth-year medical student. This is his final column.</em></p>

